g2:c.ACTION-BUTTON.g2:a.LABEL: Start test in development mode w/o test driver

g2:c.FREE-TEXT.g2:a.TEXT:
This test is based upon wink video attached to GENSYMCID-1779. It ensures that "After cloning an encapsulator with a gdl-data-connection in, and a stub with a gdl-path-display connected to the corresponding gdl-data-path-connection-post on the encapsulator subworkspace, the values DO propagate from stub to the path-display".
NOTES 1. In course of running the test, some actions seem to be unnecessary, but we recognized it when our work was mostly done. 2. We tried to use non-gui procedures whenever possible, but sometims it failed and we had to fall back to mouse clicks and text search. 3. Workspaces are scaled by 0.5 to make them fit on smaller screen resolutions. If you modify this test, look at "DEV" notes in the DO-ALL-INNER procedure. 4. Some things work slowly, most noticeable is startup. We set 12 second delay, but this can prove insufficient if testing hardware is slow.
It is a library of test-related utilities. Those can be moved out to a separated module, but that's too early yet
